adviseScripts.text: D is not saying anything.
What are you doing?
Leave her alone.
You're the one who asked for this session.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I was waiting for you to ask a question.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If you don't have anything to say, then I'll leave.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Are you not going to ask me anything?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I thought you would start the conversation.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If you don't have anything to say, then I'll leave.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D turns to leave, but I stop her and proceed to have a real conversation with her.
Before you reach a decision on something,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: are there any other factors that you consider?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: What impact my decision will have on the world.
Not really. I just make my decision and go for it.
It might sound somewhat arrogant, but it's true.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Some decisions can have a significant impact on the world.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Therefore, you must deliberate on every decision you make, big or small.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Once you decide, there's no going back.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Interesting.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That is indeed one way of going about it.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: However, you cannot always live your life this way.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: There will come a time in your life
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: when you need to deliberate and weigh important factors into a decision-making process.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about the consequences of our actions.
What do you live for?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Money? Respect?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Both are important.
Neither.
I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You're the same as everyone else.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I don't believe I need to ask any further questions.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: What then?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: No, don't answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'll see for myself
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: whether your words have truth to them or not.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about what we base our lives on.
Let me ask you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Do you consider yourself a good person?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I try to walk the straight and narrow.
Yes, I consider myself a good person.
Good answer. There is no such thing as a person who is 100% good through and through.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: There are only those who try their best to do the right thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That is why I must rid this world of all evil.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: So that they do not exert their sinister influence over people like you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You speak with such confidence.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: When the time comes,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I will see whether there is truth to your words.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about being a good person.
It's a heavy load to bear...
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Your body?
The life you lead?
I was rather referring to the weight of my mission in life.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: At any rate, I feel a bit better now.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: ... Yes.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: The eternal struggle between good and evil,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: and how that pertains not only to my life, but to the lives of others.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You can say the weight of this crown is definitely the weight of life.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a serious counseling session with D.
How would you
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: make this world a cleaner place?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Get rid of all the garbage.
Reduce waste production to nothing.
Correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: We can't stop garbage from being created so
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: cleaning up as much of it as possible once it's disposed of
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: is the only way to ensure the world remains uncluttered.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Do you think that is possible?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Humans create untold amounts of waste merely by living.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: It's impossible to reduce that figure to zero.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about cleaning habits.
*Wiggle* *Wiggle*
D's bag is moving on its own...
What's wrong?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: What is in that bag?
... Nothing.
I was wondering what you were staring at.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I assume you're wondering what's inside?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You've been staring at my bag this entire time.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Are you curious about what's in it?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I nod.
Let's just say it has something to do with one of my assignments.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I can't tell you any more than that.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: For your own well-being, I suggest you don't probe any further.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I try my best not to focus on D's bag...
If you wanted to kill someone without leaving any trace,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: what kind of tool do you think you'd need?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: One that got rid of blood splatters.
I'm not too sure.
Hm.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You talk as if you have experience with this kind of thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D puts her hand on her hatchet.
... It's just something I overheard the Nikkes saying one time.
I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D removes her hand from the hatchet.
... I'll keep that in mind, then.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I figured as much.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: How could you know something like that?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You've never found yourself in a situation where you'd need something like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: ... Right?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I spend a somewhat nerve-wracking session with D.
Do you prefer the head,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: or the body?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Both are fine with me.
I can't really decide on that.
I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I'll cut it straight down the middle.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D takes out a bear-shaped cake.
What's the cake for?
I found it during a mission, but it's far too large for me to eat by myself.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'll cut it in half and we can share it.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Why not?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Are you saying you don't want to eat any of it?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Eat? What are you talking about?
D takes out a bear-shaped cake.
I found it during a mission, but it's far too large for me to eat by myself.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If you don't want any, that's your loss.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D shares the cake with me.
If at some point in time,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: there is a day I choose to go to the dark side...
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That day will never come.
I will do what has to be done and take you down.
I wouldn't be so sure. This world we live in is a capricious one.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Meaning even I can change.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If that does come to pass...
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: do whatever you must to put a stop to me. Evil must not be allowed to spread.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Understand?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: ... Yes.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I trust you to do the right thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D and I ponder about what might potentially happen in the future.
Say there is something you need to do today, but you are very tired.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: To the point you can barely keep your eyes open.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: What would you do then?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I wouldn't procrastinate and finish what I intended to do that day.
I'd save it for another day.
You and I think alike.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: One's obligations should be taken seriously.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That way, things won't pile up and overwhelm you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If you continually put things off,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: they'll pile up and eventually overwhelm you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: When that happens, your judgment is liable to be impaired.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: This is something that must never be allowed to happen.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about various tasks that needed to be done today.
It's time for our session, but D is nowhere to be seen.
*Zing*
Sorry, I'm late.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: My name's Daisy, and I'll be your counselor today.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Some counselor you are, being late to an appointment. You're fired!
Who are you...?
Very good.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I see you're quite proficient at improv.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That could come in handy for future missions.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh*
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: It seems that you're not the most adept at playing along with improv.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'll have to keep that in mind for our future missions.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I practice acting with D.
It's time for our session, but D is not here.
*Zing*
I can pick up the faint smell of blood on D.
Did you just get back from... work?
Do you want to go wash up first?
Yes.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Perhaps we should reschedule.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Don't wait up for me. Go and do whatever else you have to do.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Fine. I'll go take a shower and be right back.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If there's anything else you need to do, feel free to take care of that first.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D heads towards the shower.
Tell me.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Aren't you scared of me?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I haven't done anything wrong. Why should I be scared?
A little.
... I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D gives me a slight grin.
You're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: So long as you never do anything immoral, I'll never turn on you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I promise.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Understandable.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I can see how what I do would inspire fear in others.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about jobs.
What is atonement to you?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Doing whatever it takes to be forgiven.
Taking full responsibility for your actions.
Forgiveness?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If you murdered someone, who would forgive you?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: The one you killed? Their friends and loved ones?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: No. There is no such thing as forgiveness in that instance.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Well said.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: If you have committed a transgression,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: you must face the consequences.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Once you have sinned, that is a cross that you must bear for the rest of your life.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That to me, is what atonement is.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I, too, have my own cross to bear.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: And it will be with me for all my days.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about the repercussions of sin.
Let's say you're out for a stroll, and you suddenly see your target.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: What do you do?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I act casually and continue along my merry way.
I try to follow them.
Correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: When you are not ready,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: it is best to not act recklessly.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Otherwise, your target might catch on to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You would follow them even though you were not prepared?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Do not act recklessly.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You might give yourself away.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about dealing with different situations.
What's your favorite kind of weather?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Rainy days.
Sunny days.
I enjoy rainy days as well,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: but for a different reason than you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'd say that if you want your assassination to remain unperceived,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: don't miss out on rainy days.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I prefer rainy days.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Unlike a flurry of rain,
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: sunshine doesn't help you with washing away the smell of death. Not at all.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I check tomorrow's weather with D.
What do you like to do on your days off?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I don't take days off.
I sleep.
Don't overdo it.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: You are a human, so getting rest is imperative.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Otherwise, lack of sleep might cloud your judgment.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Smart. It's imperative that humans get adequate rest.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: To maintain good judgment, it's important to keep yourself in tip-top shape.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Don't ever forget that.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about ways of resting.
One day you receive a gift from a stranger.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: What do you do?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I check whether the gift contains anything dangerous.
I celebrate the fact I've gotten a gift.
Very good. You must be cautious at all times.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: There is no way of knowing what kind of method will be used to assassinate you.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Don't let yourself get complacent and careless.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: The slightest lapse in vigilance creates a window of opportunity for an assassin like me.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: ... Sloppy.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Why would you be that careless? You never know what could happen or how things might unfold when you're being targeted.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Don't ever forget that.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: The slightest lapse in vigilance creates a window of opportunity for an assassin like me.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: Always be on your guard.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with D about having a healthy wariness of strangers.
What do you find most admirable in a person?
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: The ability to clearly distinguish right from wrong.
The ability to come off as cold, but in reality be quite gregarious.
Incredible.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: It's as if you read my mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'll have to use that line on my next mission.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: That's a rather... unique response.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'm not sure if I could use any of that in a future mission, but
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: I'll keep it in mind, I suppose.
adviseScripts.speaker: D

adviseScripts.text: D and I converse about the traits we find admirable in others.
